<div class="section" style="margin-top:28px;">

<p style="padding-top:5px;  font-size:12pt; text-align:justify;">I am a PhD candidate at the <a href="http://www.uic.edu">University of Illinois at Chicago</a> in the <a href="http://www.cs.uic.edu">Department of Computer Science</a>, where I am being advised by <a href="http://cs.uic.edu/~ckanich">Chris Kanich</a>. I also closely collaborate with <a href="http://www.blaseur.com/">Blase Ur</a> and <a href="http://www1.icsi.berkeley.edu/~narseo/">Narseo Vallina-Rodriguez</a>. 
<!-- I received my undergraduate degree in Electrical Engineering from the <a href="http://www.lums.edu.pk"> Lahore University of Managment Sciences (LUMS)</a>, Pakistan before I moved to Chicago in 2015. -->
  
<p style="padding-top:20px; padding-bottom:0px; font-size:12pt; text-align:justify;">My research interests span the domain of security and privacy on the Internet. I focus on understanding online privacy, socio-technical aspects of cybercrime, and human factors in security. I am also interested in usable security, cybercrime economics, and Internet censorship. 

A lot of my work incorporates insights from empirical analysis to suggest primitives in order to improve the security, reliability and the performance of the Internet.</p>

<p style="font-size:13pt; padding-top:30px; padding-bottom:0px; color: #3284bf; font-weight:900">News Updates</p>
